
Hello fellow programmers!

   For few days I've been working on a polygon landscape renderer. Now, when
it's as finished as it never'll get, I decided to publish it with source.

   Why? Mainly because I saw a similiar demo (Magic, by Chris Egerter),
which was great, but didn't include any sources.

   I took heightfieldmap and ground-textures-map from Chirs' demo (mine were
terrible =)
and documented my sources a bit. I wasn't able to get my E-mail trough,
so I couldn't ask a permission from Chris. Sorry Chris.

   About the sources: The code is for DJGPP 2.?. No assembler code is
included (I'm not very used to this AT&T syntax yet :[ ). I haven't included
my graphics sources (grp.cc is missing), but there's header and object file.
All other sources are included.

   MCPET.CC/.H is the actual rendering engine.
   FLY.CC/.H is main program.
   TPF.CC/.H is texture mapping function. (In C++ !!!!)
   KEYBOARD.H/.O keyboard handler.
   FIXED2.H 16.16 fixed point functions
   FIXED.H 24.8 fixed point functions

The keyboard handler isn't mine. It's written by Martynas Kunigelis, but
I can't find the original zip. If you can tell me, where to get it, E-mail
me.

   I've also included a batch-file (compile.bat), by which you can compile
fly.exe. 

I've also included executable, fly.exe. You can use keys:

      ESC         -          Quit
      UP          -          Increase speed
      DOWN        -          Decrease speed
      LEFT/RIGHT  -          Turn left/right
      Q/A         -          Go up/down
      PGUP/PGDWN  -          Look up/down
      U/I         -          Increase/Decrease tilt

If you have any comments, questions, suggestions, flames... Anything, E-mail
me to zaphod@sci.fi.

BTW Textures don't tile very well, but they're quite good to be drawn by me...

CYA

Aatu Koskensilta (Zaphod.B) 1.8.1996 (That is 1st of 8th month, to you who
